The Kilifi government is recruiting 78 health workers as a stopgap to the ongoing strike.Acting Health chief officer Baha Nguma on Tuesday told journalists in his office the administration has hired retired medical practitioners.&ldquo;The 36 qualified nurses, 12 clinical officers, 12 pharmacists and 18 medical officers will be posted to the Kilifi County Hospital, Malindi Subcounty and Mariakani Subcounty hospitals,&rdquo; he said.